devdoc.title: Smart Escrow Contract for swapping eth to btc using oracliize

__callback(bytes32,string).notice: Oraclize call back function invoking payout processpayable because oraclize call needs gas and this is preventing fraud

depositEther(string,uint256).notice: Deposited by sender how wants to get Bitcoin for his Ether assigning the contract valuesThe Bitcoin Address should  be new and not have any prior Transacitions (checked by UI) and should not exsist in mapping!

getTransaction(string,string).notice: Oraclize call, Bitcoin sender calls this function with his  and recipient Address which will invoke call back functionpayable because oraclize call needs gas and this is preventing fraud
